# Selenium Practice Automation

This project contains automated UI tests created to practice **Selenium test automation** using the demo website:

https://the-internet.herokuapp.com/

The goal of this repository is to strengthen automation testing skills by working with real-world web testing scenarios.

## Purpose

This project is focused on improving the following automation testing skills:

- Selenium WebDriver usage
- UI element interaction
- Test structure and organization
- Handling dynamic web elements
- Practicing common QA automation scenarios

The website used in this project provides many examples of typical UI behaviors found in real applications.

## Technologies Used

- Java
- Selenium WebDriver
- JUnit / Test framework
- Maven
- Visual Studio Code

## Test Scenarios

The project includes automated tests for different components of the demo site, such as:

- Login authentication
- Dropdown menus
- Checkboxes
- Alerts
- Dynamic loading
- File upload
- Form inputs
- Navigation elements

Each test focuses on interacting with different types of UI elements and verifying expected behavior.

